\newlabel{tab:sim_spec}{{3.2}{43}{The specifiactions of FRB catalog simulations. HEALPix \citep {gorski2005healpix} is an algorithm to pixellize as an image with certain resolution. The resolution parameter $N_\mathrm {side}$ can be understood as the inverse of the diameter of one pixel on the map $\theta _\mathrm {min} \approx 1/N_\mathrm {side}$}{table.caption.16}{}}
